Fabricius Luscinus who was opposed to Pyrrhus In B.c. 275 he was Censor, and distinguished himself by the severity of his proceedings for putting down luxurious habits. In particular he and his colleague, Q. Aemilius Papus, are said to have degraded a senator, P.
